
                                                              COMPTIA NETWORK:
Here are short notes on the classes of IPv4 addresses:
Class A:
  Range:1.0.0.0 to 126.0.0.0
  Default subnet mask:255.0.0.0
  First octet is used for network ID, remaining 3 for host ID

Class B:
  Range:128.0.0.0 to 191.255.0.0
  Supports medium-sized networks(up to 65,534 hosts)
  Default subnet mask:255.255.0.0
  First 2 octets for network ID, remaining 2 for host ID

Class C:
  Range:192.0.0.0 to 223.255.255.0
  Supports small networks (up to 254 hosts)
  Default subnet mask:255.255.255.0
  First 3 octets for network ID, last octet for host ID

Class D:
  Range:224.0.0.0 to 239.255.255.255
  Used for multicasting (not for normal host addressing)
  No subnet mask

